<TITLE> Australia are top seeds for 2008 Champions Trophy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, March 13 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Holders Australia are the top seeds for the ICC Champions Trophy to be staged in Pakistan this September, the International Cricket Council said on Thursday. Australia, also the one-day World Cup champions, are grouped with India, former winners West Indies and Pakistan in Group A. Former champions South Africa and New Zealand, Sri Lanka and England are in Group B. The groupings for the biennial tournament were decided on the basis of the official one-day rankings as of March 12, an ICC news release said. The ICC decided three years ago to prune the field to eight teams from 10, following criticism of an unwieldy tournament. The two top teams in each group after the round robin stage will qualify for the knockout semi-finals. The tournament schedule and venues will be announced later. The groups (seedings in brackets): Group A: Australia (1), India (4), Pakistan (5), West Indies (8) Group B: South Africa (2), New Zealand (3), Sri Lanka (6), England (7
